Description: Fragment of oval handle from a Thasian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine micaceous light brown-beige. Rectangular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription and sword or dolphin symbol.
Curator's comments: Name Aristophon. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p. 102, 25. Compare Ch. Tchokev, The Athenian Agora xxxvii, 128, no. 125.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0016)
